  "prompt": "How can I add more topics here in Quora?",
  "response": "To add more topics to Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log in to Quora:** Ensure you are logged into your Quora account.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Question Page:**\n   - If you are asking a question, click on the \"Ask Question\" button, which is typically located at the top right corner of the Quora homepage.\n\n3. **Add a Question (if applicable):**\n   - Type in your question in the provided field.\n\n4. **Add Topics to Your Question:**\n   - After typing your question, you will see a box labeled \"Add Topics\" or \"Topics\" below your question. Click on this box.\n   - Start typing the name of the topic you want to add. Quora will suggest topics based on what you type.\n   - Select the appropriate topics from the suggestion list. You can add multiple topics by repeating this process.\n\n5. **Save Your Question:**\n   - Once you have added all relevant topics, click on the \"Add Question\" or \"Done\" button to post your question with the associated topics.\n\nIf you want to follow more topics (not adding them to a question):\n\n1. **Navigate to Interests:**\n   - Click on your profile picture to access the dropdown menu, then select \"Interests.\"\n\n2. **Browse or Search for Topics:**\n   - You can browse through the suggested topics or use the search bar to find specific topics of interest.\n\n3. **Follow Topics:**\n   - Once you find a topic you are interested in, click \"Follow\" next to the topic name to add it to your list of followed topics.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to add and follow more topics on Quora, thereby tailoring your feed and engaging more with the subjects that interest you.",
